# Data Access Patterns

## Data Retrieval — Server Components Only

Always fetch data in Server Components. Never fetch directly in Client Components.

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD — Server Component
export default async function DeckList() {
  const { userId } = await auth();
  const decks = await db.query.decks.findMany({
    where: eq(decks.userId, userId),
  });
  return <ul>{decks.map(d => <li key={d.id}>{d.name}</li>)}</ul>;
}
```

## Mutations — Server Actions Only

All inserts, updates, and deletes must be done via Server Actions. Never mutate data from a Client Component directly.

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD — Server Action in its own file or co-located with "use server"
"use server";

export async function createDeck(input: CreateDeckInput) {
  const { userId } = await auth();
  if (!userId) throw new Error("Unauthorized");

  const parsed = createDeckSchema.safeParse(input);
  if (!parsed.success) throw new Error("Invalid input");

  await db.insert(decks).values({ ...parsed.data, userId });
}
```

## Validation — Always Use Zod

Every server action must validate its input with Zod before touching the database.

```typescript
import { z } from "zod";

const createDeckSchema = z.object({
  name: z.string().min(1).max(100),
});

type CreateDeckInput = z.infer<typeof createDeckSchema>;
```

## Rules

- Never use `FormData` as a server action parameter type — always use a typed object
- Define a Zod schema and derive the TypeScript type from it via `z.infer<>`
- Always validate with `.safeParse()` and handle the error case before proceeding
